pan style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr style="height:3.5pt"><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:120.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Phil Minor</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:333.1pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr style="height:3.5pt"><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:120.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Colin Howard</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:333.1pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr></table><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Advisory Committee on Dangerous Pathogens TSE Sub Group Terms of Reference </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">“To provide ACDP as requested with practical, scientifically based advice on the assessment and the management of risks from transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs).  This advice should be in relation to food safety, public and animal health issues, taking appropriate account of present scientific uncertainty and assumptions in formulating advice on risk.  To handle issues as referred, taking into account the work of other relevant bodies."</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Advisory Committee on Dangerous Pathogens TSE Sub Group Work Plan for 2013/2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.1pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To review, revise and update the current range of TSE guidance* in collaboration with stakeholders</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.1pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To review Annex G of the TSE guidance* on specialist equipment in collaboration with stakeholders</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.1pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To publish an additional Annex to the TSE guidance* to provide comprehensive and up-to-date advice on surgical procedures involving medium risk tissue</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.1pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To review and update as necessary Annex J in collaboration with the Society of British Neurological Surgeons</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.1pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Provide advice, if needed, on new issues arising from local patient notifications of increased CJD risk.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To review evidence of transmission of vCJD via surgery</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To review scenarios and epidemiology associated with TSE prevalence studies</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To review, in conjunction with the UK Blood Services Prion Working Group, the development of prototype blood tests for abnormal prion protein</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To review the multiple strain hypothesis.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">*The TSE guidance referred to above is the “Transmissible spongiform encephalopathy agents: safe working and the prevention of infection” first published in 2003 and available from: </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/guidance-from-the-acdp-tse-risk-management-subgroup-formerly-tse-working-group"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/guidance-from-the-acdp-tse-risk-management-subgroup-formerly-tse-working-group</span></a><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(it also forms Appendix C of this evidence submission)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Appendix E - CJD IP Organs and Tissue Position Statement</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">CJD Incidents Panel: Organ and Tissue Position Statement – September 2012 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">[NB The CJD Incidents Panel was dissolved in March 2013]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The CJD Incidents panel developed an organs and tissues statement to capture decisions and discussions arising from the advice considered and given in relation to incidents over a number of years.  The following text was not published but provided an outline from which the Panel and the secretariat could provide consistent advice on any further incidents concerning organs and tissues.  It is intended that this position statement will be reviewed periodically or as required.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Use of donated organs and tissues</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Panel should not advise clinicians on the use of organs and tissues donated by people with, at risk of, or with a positive test for CJD or vCJD.  Members considered that Advisory Committee on Safety of Blood, Tissues and Organs (SaBTO) was best placed to give advice on these issues.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This does not affect the Panel’s advice to ‘at risk’ patients, not to donate organs or tissues.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Donors who test positive for vCJD at post mortem</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Incidents involving asymptomatic donors who test positive for vCJD at post mortem, should be managed in the same way as incidents involving donors with symtomatic vCJD.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Type of organs and tissues from donors with vCJD</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There was insufficient evidence on tissue infectivity levels to distinguish between the risks posed by different organs and tissues donated by patients with vCJD. Incidents involving all types of tissues and organs from donors with vCJD, including processed and unprocessed bone, should be managed in the same way. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Management of recipients</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Patients who receive any tissue or organ from donors with vCJD, or donors who test positive for vCJD at post mortem, should be considered ‘at risk’ of vCJD for public health purposes. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Patients who receive Haematopoietic stem cells HSC or</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">posterior eye tissues from donors with CJD should be considered ‘at risk’ of CJD for public health purposes. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">No actions are required for patients who have received any organs or other tissues from donors with CJD.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In general, no actions are required for patients who have received tissues or organs from asymptomatic donors ‘at risk’ of vCJD or CJD. The exceptions to this are discussed in the next section ‘Reverse Risks’.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Reverse risks</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Donors of tissues or organs to recipients, who later develop vCJD, should be assessed and managed as if they had donated blood components i.e. as ‘at risk’ for public health purposes.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Recipients of any other tissues/organs from those donors (who have given tissues/organs to a recipient who developed vCJD), should be assessed and managed as if they had received blood components i.e. as ‘at risk’ for public health purposes.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Donors of posterior eye tissues</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or HSC to recipients who later develop CJD, should also be assessed and managed as for vCJD implicated blood components i.e. as ‘at risk’ for public health purposes. No actions are required for donors of organs</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or other tissues to recipients who later develop CJD.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:10pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Recipients of posterior eye tissues or HSC from those donors (who have given posterior eye tissues</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or HSC to a recipient who developed CJD) should be assessed and managed as for vCJD implicated blood components i.e. as ‘at risk’ for public health purposes. No actions are required for the recipients of organs and other tissues from these donors.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Table 1: Action for organ/tissue recipients: by donor status and organ/tissue type</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt; width:496.15pt"><tr><td rowspan="2" style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:middle; width:92.2pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Tissue/organ type</span></p></td><td colspan="5" style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:403.95pt"><p style="margin:6pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Donor status</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:middle; width:70.85pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">vCJD case</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:super">1</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:middle; width:63.8pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">CJD case</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:super">2</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:middle; width:92.15pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">At risk of vCJD following donation to vCJD recipient</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#00000